// Regression: m.get(k).unwrap_or(default) on an int-valued map. HashMap.get returns
// the raw value (not an Option), so routing through OptionInt_unwrap_or passed a raw
// int where an OptionInt was expected → C type error. Now lowers to the runtime's
// key-or-default lookup. (2026-07)
fn main() {
    var m = {"a": 10, "b": 20}
    println(m.get("a").unwrap_or(-1))
    println(m.get("missing").unwrap_or(-1))
    var v = m.get("b").unwrap_or(0)
    println(v)
}
// EXPECT: 10
// EXPECT: -1
// EXPECT: 20
